                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in fornt of the Narasiṁhasvāmin shrine in the Kallēśvara temple.</p>						                            
                            <p>1032 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This is dated the cyclic year Plava, Māgha, śu. 15, Sunday. Palaeographically the record may be assigned to about the 11th century and the details correspond to 1032, A.D., January 27.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It registers a gift of land to the god Narasiṁhadēva of Vithapura by the fifty <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> Bāguḷi called <hi rend="italic">Hariśchandradatti.</hi></p>						
                            
                        </summary>
